Package gradecomputor

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    computerAnimatedBackground
    This Class is supposed to render the animated plot background from GIFs.
    computorCategoryAxis
    This is a custom Class for suppressing the unnecessary labels shown on the x-axis of the plot.
    computorCSVReader
    This Class responsible for reading the CSV (Comma-Separated Values) file and obtain the relevant information for the display and grade judgment.
    computorCSVWriter
    This Class responsible for writing the CSV (Comma-Separated Values) file as per the University's specified instructions for Registrar office upload.
    computorItemLabelGenerator
    This is a custom Class overwriting the JFreeChart's default series legend labels with the appropriate student counts as series legend labels.
    computorMainWindow
    This Class is responsible for the display of the student lineup and relevant information for the judgment of their grades.
    computorMarker
    This Class contains the information about the Markers displayed on the plot.
    computorMarkerConfigPanel
    This Class is displays the collective information about the Markers (in buffer) and their configurations.
    computorMarkerEditor
    A JPanel for specific Marker creation and configuration.
    computorMarkerRenderer
    A custom renderer for generating dynamical Markers in the plot with high sensitivity to the user interaction.
    computorProductInformationPanel
    A JPanel for describing the purpose of the application and current state of the system it is running on.
    computorString
    A Class useful for parsing the CSV text.
    computorStudent
    This Class is responsible for storing students' name, score and grade.
    computorValueMarker
    This Class is for the custom Marker with additional complexities.
    GradeComputor
